	  texUnit-callback

2005-10-22 22:50  tigital

	* GL_VERSION_1_1 check only (there's no GL_VERSION_1_0_ on osx!)

2005-10-21 14:49  zmoelnig

	* improved threaded movie-player: use select() instead of usleep()
	  (should be more portable) when the grabThread returns no frame
	  (NULL), a "bang" is emitted at render-time. the user gets a
	  chance to immediately react on that and reset the frame# to
	  something valid.  when threaded, this will force the changed
	  frame to be read in the main-thread (luckily the grabthread is
	  locked by the mutex)

