	  14:18:07 +0000

2005-07-03 20:42  zmoelnig

	* updated build-system after having a look at the Gnu-make
	  documentation what's better:	       SOURCES are generated on the
	  fly	     .cpp-files containing whitespaces are ignored (rather
	  than crashing the build.process)  dependencies are calculated on
	  a per-file basis (rather than via Make.depend)   better
	  subdirectory handling (not for "clean"ing though)	   better
	  check for "strip" (partly taken from wine)

