2004-02-02 12:15  zmoelnig

	* put QT-loader *after* the AVI-loader, because QT sometimes
	  crashes when having loaded AVI's and tries to load QT's
	  afterwards.  so AVI is now handled by the built in (for win)
	  routines, and QuickTime is only used if it fails

